1. create a server
2. install nginx ( sudo dnf install -y nginx ), run systemctl start nginx 
3. have a look at ( /etc/nginx/nginx.conf )
4. copy the server directive from this file to /etc/nginx/conf.d/<yourname>.conf
5. send me your public IP
6. change the server name to <yourname>.omarwsaleh.com
7. change your root directory to  /usr/share/nginx/<yourlastname>
8. create /usr/share/nginx/<yourlastname>
9. create index.html in /usr/share/nginx/<yourlastname>
10. remove the line that starts with "include"
11. run ngint -t ( to verify that your conf is correct )
12. run systemctl reload nginx ( to reload the new conf )


Task2
1. Install nginx on your local machine and start nginx
  a. remove defaul server directive conf from /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
2. you can always test specific server name using 'curl -H "Host: <servername>" http://localhost'
3. configure two virtual hosts 
   1. xyz.com  served from /usr/share/nginx/pythonapp  (index.html < hello from python app )
   2. example.com served from /usr/share/nginx/rubyapp (index.html < hello from ruby app )
4. nginx -t 
5. systemctl reload ngnix
6. test using curl 


Task 3
1. start a server and install httpd using (dnf install httpd -y )
2. start httpd ( systemctl start httpd )
3. configure nginx to be a reverse proxy for that server 
   https://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_upstream_module.html
4. I want the reverse proxy to be accessible using servername "new_example.com"



Task 2 && Task 3 => xyz.conf, example.conf , new_example.conf
